# Cara 2: Looping + html_node()/html_element()

library(rvest)
library(stringr)

remove_space <- function(str){str_replace_all(str, '\\s+', ' ')}

scrape_card <- function(card){
  url <- card %>% html_node('a') %>% html_attr('href')
  brand <- card %>% html_node('.mod-card__title') %>% html_text(trim = T) %>% remove_space()
  price <- card %>% html_node('.mod-card__price__total') %>% html_text(trim = T) %>% remove_space()
  price_cash <- card %>% html_node('.mod-card__price-cash') %>% html_text(trim = T)
  tag <- card %>% html_node('.mod-card__car-other') %>% html_elements('span') %>% 
    html_text() %>% paste(collapse = ',')
  feature <- card %>% html_node('.mod-card__high-tag-list') %>% html_elements('span') %>% 
    html_text() %>% paste(collapse = ',')
  
  return(c(brand = brand, 
           price = price, 
           price_cash = price_cash, 
           feature = feature, 
           tag = tag,
           url = url))
}

url <- 'https://www.carsome.id/beli-mobil-bekas'
page <- read_html(url)
cards <- page %>% html_nodes('.mod-card')

cars <- cards %>% 
  lapply(scrape_card) %>% 
  do.call(rbind, .) %>% 
  as.data.frame()

cars

library(stringr)

url <- 'https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/premier-league/top-scorers'
script_nodes <- read_html(url) %>% html_nodes("script")
top_players <- script_nodes[length(script_nodes)-4] %>%
  as.character %>%
  str_replace(".*?\\{(.+)\\}.*", "\\1") %>%
  str_replace(".*?(\\{.+\\}).*", "\\1") %>%
  fromJSON

rank_by_goal <- top_players$body$sbl$football$playersRankedByGoals$standing
rank_by_goal
rank_by_assist <- top_players$body$sbl$football$playersRankedByAssists$standing
rank_by_assist
